#. class="division">
msgctxt "dn25:1.1"
msgid "Dīgha Nikāya 25"
msgstr "Long Discourses 25"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "dn25:2.1"
msgid "Udumbarikasutta"
msgstr "The Lion’s Roar at Udumbarikā’s Monastery"

#. </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "dn25:3.1"
msgid "1. Nigrodhaparibbājakavatthu"
msgstr "On the Wanderer Nigrodha"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="1"></a><a class="wp" id="wp1"></a><a class="pts"
#. id="pts3.36"></a>
msgctxt "dn25:4.1"
msgid "<span class=\"evam\">Evaṃ me sutaṃ—​</span>"
msgstr "<span class=”evam”>So I have heard.</span>"

msgctxt "dn25:4.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā rājagahe viharati gijjhakūṭe pabbate."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Rājagaha, on the Vulture’s Peak "
"Mountain."

# RD and MW oddly have "discourse to the udumbarikans". Comm explains the term as "Udumbarikāya paribbājakārāmeti udumbarikāya deviyā santake paribbājakārāme" In Chinese, DA 8 has "烏暫婆利梵志女林" The forest of the Udumbara brahmin lady", MA 104 has "優曇婆邏林" Udumbara forest", T 11 has "烏曇末梨園" "Udumbara park".
msgctxt "dn25:4.3"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena nigrodho paribbājako udumbarikāya paribbājakārāme "
"paṭivasati mahatiyā paribbājakaparisāya saddhiṃ tiṃsamattehi "
"paribbājakasatehi."
msgstr ""
"Now at that time the wanderer Nigrodha was residing in the lady Udumbarikā’s "
"monastery for wanderers, together with a large assembly of three thousand "
"wanderers."

#. VAR: divassa → divādivasseva (s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "dn25:4.4"
msgid ""
"Atha kho sandhāno gahapati divā divassa rājagahā nikkhami bhagavantaṃ "
"dassanāya."
msgstr ""
"Then the householder Sandhana left Rājagaha in the middle of the day to see "
"the Buddha."

msgctxt "dn25:4.5"
msgid "Atha kho sandhānassa gahapatissa etadahosi:"
msgstr "Then it occurred to him:"

msgctxt "dn25:4.6"
msgid "“akālo kho bhagavantaṃ dassanāya."
msgstr "“It’s the wrong time to see the Buddha, "

msgctxt "dn25:4.7"
msgid "Paṭisallīno bhagavā."
msgstr "as he’s in retreat."

msgctxt "dn25:4.8"
msgid "Manobhāvanīyānampi bhikkhūnaṃ asamayo dassanāya."
msgstr "And it’s the wrong time to see the esteemed mendicants,"

msgctxt "dn25:4.9"
msgid "Paṭisallīnā manobhāvanīyā bhikkhū."
msgstr "as they’re in retreat."

msgctxt "dn25:4.10"
msgid ""
"Yannūnāhaṃ yena udumbarikāya paribbājakārāmo, yena nigrodho paribbājako "
"tenupasaṅkameyyan”ti."
msgstr ""
"Why don’t I visit the wanderer Nigrodha at the lady Udumbarikā’s monastery "
"for wanderers?”"

msgctxt "dn25:4.11"
msgid ""
"Atha kho sandhāno gahapati yena udumbarikāya paribbājakārāmo, tenupasaṅkami."
msgstr "So he went to the monastery of the wanderers."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="2"></a><a class="wp" id="wp2"></a><a class="pts"
#. id="pts3.37"></a>
msgctxt "dn25:5.1"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena nigrodho paribbājako mahatiyā paribbājakaparisāya "
"saddhiṃ nisinno hoti unnādiniyā uccāsaddamahāsaddāya anekavihitaṃ "
"tiracchānakathaṃ kathentiyā."
msgstr ""
"Now at that time, Nigrodha was sitting together with a large assembly of "
"wanderers making an uproar, a dreadful racket. They engaged in all kinds of "
"unworthy talk, such as"

msgctxt "dn25:5.2"
msgid "Seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn25:5.3"
msgid ""
"rājakathaṃ corakathaṃ mahāmattakathaṃ senākathaṃ bhayakathaṃ yuddhakathaṃ "
"annakathaṃ pānakathaṃ vatthakathaṃ sayanakathaṃ mālākathaṃ gandhakathaṃ "
"ñātikathaṃ yānakathaṃ gāmakathaṃ nigamakathaṃ nagarakathaṃ janapadakathaṃ "
"itthikathaṃ sūrakathaṃ visikhākathaṃ kumbhaṭṭhānakathaṃ pubbapetakathaṃ "
"nānattakathaṃ lokakkhāyikaṃ samuddakkhāyikaṃ itibhavābhavakathaṃ iti vā."
msgstr ""
"talk about kings, bandits, and ministers; talk about armies, threats, and "
"wars; talk about food, drink, clothes, and beds; talk about garlands and "
"fragrances; talk about family, vehicles, villages, towns, cities, and "
"countries; talk about women and heroes; street talk and well talk; talk "
"about the departed; motley talk; tales of land and sea; and talk about being "
"reborn in this or that state of existence."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="3"></a><a class="wp" id="wp3"></a>
msgctxt "dn25:6.1"
msgid ""
"Addasā kho nigrodho paribbājako sandhānaṃ gahapatiṃ dūratova āgacchantaṃ."
msgstr "Nigrodha saw Sandhāna coming off in the distance,"

msgctxt "dn25:6.2"
msgid "Disvā sakaṃ parisaṃ saṇṭhāpesi:"
msgstr "and hushed his own assembly:"

msgctxt "dn25:6.3"
msgid "“appasaddā bhonto hontu, mā bhonto saddamakattha."
msgstr "“Be quiet, good sirs, don’t make a sound."

msgctxt "dn25:6.4"
msgid "Ayaṃ samaṇassa gotamassa sāvako āgacchati sandhāno gahapati."
msgstr "The householder Sandhāna, a disciple of the ascetic Gotama, is coming."

msgctxt "dn25:6.5"
msgid ""
"Yāvatā kho pana samaṇassa gotamassa sāvakā gihī odātavasanā rājagahe "
"paṭivasanti, ayaṃ tesaṃ aññataro sandhāno gahapati."
msgstr ""
"He is included among the white-clothed lay disciples of the ascetic Gotama, "
"who is residing near Rājagaha."

msgctxt "dn25:6.6"
msgid ""
"Appasaddakāmā kho panete āyasmanto appasaddavinītā, appasaddassa vaṇṇavādino."
msgstr ""
"Such venerables like the quiet, are educated to be quiet, and praise quiet."

msgctxt "dn25:6.7"
msgid "Appeva nāma appasaddaṃ parisaṃ viditvā upasaṅkamitabbaṃ maññeyyā”ti."
msgstr ""
"Hopefully if he sees that our assembly is quiet he’ll see fit to approach.”"

msgctxt "dn25:6.8"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, te paribbājakā tuṇhī ahesuṃ."
msgstr "Then those wanderers fell silent."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="4"></a><a class="wp" id="wp4"></a><a class="pts"
#. id="pts3.38"></a>
#. VAR: kho → ca (pts1)
msgctxt "dn25:7.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho sandhāno gahapati yena nigrodho paribbājako tenupasaṅkami, "
"upasaṅkamitvā nigrodhena paribbājakena saddhiṃ sammodi."
msgstr ""
"Then Anāthapiṇḍika went up to the wanderer Nigrodha, and exchanged greetings "
"with him. "

msgctxt "dn25:7.2"
msgid "Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi."
msgstr ""
"When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he sat down to one "
"side,"

msgctxt "dn25:7.3"
msgid ""
"Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho sandhāno gahapati nigrodhaṃ paribbājakaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "and said to Nigrodha:"

msgctxt "dn25:7.4"
msgid ""
"“aññathā kho ime bhonto aññatitthiyā paribbājakā saṅgamma samāgamma unnādino "
"uccāsaddamahāsaddā anekavihitaṃ tiracchānakathaṃ anuyuttā viharanti."
msgstr ""
"“The way the wanderers make an uproar as they sit together and talk about "
"all kinds of unworthy topics is one thing."

msgctxt "dn25:7.5"
msgid "Seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn25:7.6"
msgid "rājakathaṃ …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn25:7.7"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn25:7.8"
msgid "itibhavābhavakathaṃ iti vā."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn25:7.9"
msgid ""
"Aññathā kho pana so bhagavā araññavanapatthāni pantāni senāsanāni paṭisevati "
"appasaddāni appanigghosāni vijanavātāni manussarāhasseyyakāni "
"paṭisallānasāruppānī”ti."
msgstr ""
"It’s quite different to the way the Buddha frequents remote lodgings in the "
"wilderness and the forest that are quiet and still, far from the madding "
"crowd, remote from human settlements, and appropriate for retreat.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="5"></a><a class="wp" id="wp5"></a>
msgctxt "dn25:8.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, nigrodho paribbājako sandhānaṃ gahapatiṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "When Sandhāna said this, Nigrodha said to him:"

msgctxt "dn25:8.2"
msgid ""
"“yagghe, gahapati, jāneyyāsi, kena samaṇo gotamo saddhiṃ sallapati, kena "
"sākacchaṃ samāpajjati, kena paññāveyyattiyaṃ samāpajjati?"
msgstr ""
"“Surely, householder, you should know better! With whom does the ascetic "
"Gotama converse? With whom does he engage in discussion? With whom does he "
"achieve proficiency in wisdom?"

msgctxt "dn25:8.3"
msgid ""
"Suññāgārahatā samaṇassa gotamassa paññā aparisāvacaro samaṇo gotamo nālaṃ "
"sallāpāya."
msgstr ""
"Staying in empty huts has destroyed the ascetic Gotama’s wisdom. Not "
"frequenting assemblies, he is unable to hold a discussion."

#. VAR: antamantāneva → antapantāneva (s1-3)
msgctxt "dn25:8.4"
msgid "So antamantāneva sevati."
msgstr "He just lurks on the periphery."

msgctxt "dn25:8.5"
msgid "Seyyathāpi nāma gokāṇā pariyantacārinī antamantāneva sevati."
msgstr ""
"He’s just like the nilgai antelope, circling around and lurking on the "
"periphery."

msgctxt "dn25:8.6"
msgid "Evameva suññāgārahatā samaṇassa gotamassa paññā;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn25:8.7"
msgid "aparisāvacaro samaṇo gotamo;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn25:8.8"
msgid "nālaṃ sallāpāya."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn25:8.9"
msgid "So antamantāneva sevati."
msgstr ""

# orodheyyāmā is unclear. I follow comm: Orodheyyāmāti vinandheyyāma. Pūritaghaṭo hi ito cito ca parivattetvā na suvinandhanīyo hoti. Rittako yathāruci parivattetvā sakkā hoti vinandhituṃ, evameva hatapaññatāya rittakumbhisadisaṃ samaṇaṃ gotamaṃ vādavinandhanena samantā vinandhissāmāti vadati.
#. VAR: saṃsādeyyāma → saṃhareyyāma (mr)
msgctxt "dn25:8.10"
msgid ""
"Iṅgha, gahapati, samaṇo gotamo imaṃ parisaṃ āgaccheyya, ekapañheneva naṃ "
"saṃsādeyyāma, tucchakumbhīva naṃ maññe orodheyyāmā”ti."
msgstr ""
"Please, householder, let the ascetic Gotama come to this assembly. I’ll sink "
"him with just one question! I’ll roll him over and wrap him up like an empty "
"pot!”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="6"></a><a class="wp" id="wp6"></a><a class="pts"
#. id="pts3.39"></a>
msgctxt "dn25:9.1"
msgid ""
"Assosi kho bhagavā dibbāya sotadhātuyā visuddhāya atikkantamānusikāya "
"sandhānassa gahapatissa nigrodhena paribbājakena saddhiṃ imaṃ kathāsallāpaṃ."
msgstr ""
"With clairaudience that is purified and superhuman, the Buddha heard this "
"discussion between the householder Sandhāna and the wanderer Nigrodha."

msgctxt "dn25:9.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā gijjhakūṭā pabbatā orohitvā yena sumāgadhāya tīre "
"moranivāpo tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr ""
"Then the Buddha descended Vulture’s Peak Mountain and went to the peacock’s "
"feeding ground on the bank of the Sumāgadhā,"

msgctxt "dn25:9.3"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā sumāgadhāya tīre moranivāpe abbhokāse caṅkami."
msgstr "where he practiced walking meditation in the open air."

msgctxt "dn25:9.4"
msgid ""
"Addasā kho nigrodho paribbājako bhagavantaṃ sumāgadhāya tīre moranivāpe "
"abbhokāse caṅkamantaṃ."
msgstr "Nigrodha saw him,"

msgctxt "dn25:9.5"
msgid "Disvāna sakaṃ parisaṃ saṇṭhāpesi:"
msgstr "and hushed his own assembly:"

msgctxt "dn25:9.6"
msgid ""
"“appasaddā bhonto hontu, mā bhonto saddamakattha, ayaṃ samaṇo gotamo "
"sumāgadhāya tīre moranivāpe abbhokāse caṅkamati."
msgstr ""
"“Be quiet, good sirs, don’t make a sound. The ascetic Gotama is walking "
"meditation on the bank of the Sumāgadhā."

msgctxt "dn25:9.7"
msgid "Appasaddakāmo kho pana so āyasmā, appasaddassa vaṇṇavādī."
msgstr "The venerable likes quiet and praises quiet."

msgctxt "dn25:9.8"
msgid "Appeva nāma appasaddaṃ parisaṃ viditvā upasaṅkamitabbaṃ maññeyya."
msgstr ""
"Hopefully if he sees that our assembly is quiet he’ll see fit to approach."

msgctxt "dn25:9.9"
msgid ""
"Sace samaṇo gotamo imaṃ parisaṃ āgaccheyya, imaṃ taṃ pañhaṃ puccheyyāma:"
msgstr "If he comes, I’ll ask him this question:"

msgctxt "dn25:9.10"
msgid ""
"‘ko nāma so, bhante, bhagavato dhammo, yena bhagavā sāvake vineti, yena "
"bhagavatā sāvakā vinītā assāsappattā paṭijānanti ajjhāsayaṃ "
"ādibrahmacariyan’”ti?"
msgstr ""
"‘Sir, what teaching do you use to guide your disciples, through which they "
"claim solace in the fundamental purpose of the spiritual life?’”"

msgctxt "dn25:9.11"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, te paribbājakā tuṇhī ahesuṃ."
msgstr "Then those wanderers fell silent."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn25:10.1"
msgid "2. Tapojigucchāvāda"
msgstr "Mortification in Disgust of Sin"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="7"></a><a class="wp" id="wp7"></a><a class="pts"
#. id="pts3.40"></a>
msgctxt "dn25:11.1"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā yena nigrodho paribbājako tenupasaṅkami."
msgstr "Then the Buddha went up to the wanderer Nigrodha,"

msgctxt "dn25:11.2"
msgid "Atha kho nigrodho paribbājako bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "who said to him:"

msgctxt "dn25:11.3"
msgid "“etu kho, bhante, bhagavā, svāgataṃ, bhante, bhagavato."
msgstr "“Come, Blessed One! Welcome, Blessed One!"

msgctxt "dn25:11.4"
msgid "Cirassaṃ kho, bhante, bhagavā imaṃ pariyāyamakāsi yadidaṃ idhāgamanāya."
msgstr "It’s been a long time since you took the opportunity to come here."

msgctxt "dn25:11.5"
msgid "Nisīdatu, bhante, bhagavā, idamāsanaṃ paññattan”ti."
msgstr "Please, sir, sit down, this seat is ready.”"

msgctxt "dn25:11.6"
msgid "Nisīdi bhagavā paññatte āsane."
msgstr "The Buddha sat on the seat spread out,"

msgctxt "dn25:11.7"
msgid ""
"Nigrodhopi kho paribbājako aññataraṃ nīcāsanaṃ gahetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi."
msgstr "while Nigrodha took a low seat and sat to one side."

msgctxt "dn25:11.8"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho nigrodhaṃ paribbājakaṃ bhagavā etadavoca:"
msgstr "The Buddha said to him:"

msgctxt "dn25:11.9"
msgid ""
"“kāya nuttha, nigrodha, etarahi kathāya sannisinnā, kā ca pana vo "
"antarākathā vippakatā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“Nigrodha, what were you sitting talking about just now? What conversation "
"was unfinished?”"

msgctxt "dn25:11.10"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, nigrodho paribbājako bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "Nigrodha said:"

msgctxt "dn25:11.11"
msgid ""
"“idha mayaṃ, bhante, addasāma bhagavantaṃ sumāgadhāya tīre moranivāpe "
"abbhokāse caṅkamantaṃ, disvāna evaṃ avocumhā:"
msgstr "“Well, sir, I saw you walking meditation and said:"

msgctxt "dn25:11.12"
msgid ""
"‘sace samaṇo gotamo imaṃ parisaṃ āgaccheyya, imaṃ taṃ pañhaṃ puccheyyāma:"
msgstr "‘If the ascetic Gotama comes, I’ll ask him this question:"

msgctxt "dn25:11.13"
msgid ""
"“ko nāma so, bhante, bhagavato dhammo, yena bhagavā sāvake vineti, yena "
"bhagavatā sāvakā vinītā assāsappattā paṭijānanti ajjhāsayaṃ "
"ādibrahmacariyan”’ti?"
msgstr ""
"“Sir, what teaching do you use to guide your disciples, through which they "
"claim solace in the fundamental purpose of the spiritual life?”’"

msgctxt "dn25:11.14"
msgid "Ayaṃ kho no, bhante, antarākathā vippakatā;"
msgstr "This is the conversation that was unfinished"

msgctxt "dn25:11.15"
msgid "atha bhagavā anuppatto”ti."
msgstr "when the Buddha arrived.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="8"></a>
msgctxt "dn25:12.1"
msgid ""
"“Dujjānaṃ kho etaṃ, nigrodha, tayā aññadiṭṭhikena aññakhantikena "
"aññarucikena aññatrāyogena aññatrācariyakena, yenāhaṃ sāvake vinemi, yena "
"mayā sāvakā vinītā assāsappattā paṭijānanti ajjhāsayaṃ ādibrahmacariyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"“It’s hard for you to understand this, Nigrodha, since you have a different "
"view, creed, belief, practice, and tradition."

msgctxt "dn25:12.2"
msgid "Iṅgha tvaṃ maṃ, nigrodha, sake ācariyake adhijegucche pañhaṃ puccha:"
msgstr ""
"Please ask me a question about the higher mortification in disgust of sin in "
"your own tradition:"

# The idiom katham santā is unusual, but it clearly echoes evaṃ sante below
msgctxt "dn25:12.3"
msgid ""
"‘kathaṃ santā nu kho, bhante, tapojigucchā paripuṇṇā hoti, kathaṃ "
"aparipuṇṇā’”ti?"
msgstr ""
"‘How are the conditions for the mortification in disgust of sin completed, "
"and how are they incomplete?’”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="9"></a>
msgctxt "dn25:13.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, te paribbājakā unnādino uccāsaddamahāsaddā ahesuṃ:"
msgstr "When he said this, those wanderers made an uproar:"

msgctxt "dn25:13.2"
msgid ""
"“acchariyaṃ vata bho, abbhutaṃ vata bho, samaṇassa gotamassa mahiddhikatā "
"mahānubhāvatā, yatra hi nāma sakavādaṃ ṭhapessati, paravādena pavāressatī”ti."
msgstr ""
"“It’s incredible, it’s amazing! The ascetic Gotama has such power and might! "
"For he sets aside his own doctrine and invites discussion on the doctrine of "
"others!”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="10"></a><a class="wp" id="wp8"></a>
msgctxt "dn25:14.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho nigrodho paribbājako te paribbājake appasadde katvā bhagavantaṃ "
"etadavoca:"
msgstr "Then Nigrodha, having quieted those wanderers, said to the Buddha:"

msgctxt "dn25:14.2"
msgid ""
"“mayaṃ kho, bhante, tapojigucchāvādā tapojigucchāsārā tapojigucchāallīnā "
"viharāma."
msgstr ""
"“Sir, we teach mortification in disgust of sin, regarding it as essential "
"and clinging to it."

msgctxt "dn25:14.3"
msgid ""
"Kathaṃ santā nu kho, bhante, tapojigucchā paripuṇṇā hoti, kathaṃ "
"aparipuṇṇā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"How are the conditions for the mortification in disgust of sin completed, "
"and how are they incomplete?”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="11"></a><a class="pts" id="pts3.41"></a>
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn25:15.1"
msgid ""
"“Idha, nigrodha, tapassī acelako hoti muttācāro, hatthāpalekhano, "
"naehibhaddantiko, natiṭṭhabhaddantiko, nābhihaṭaṃ, na uddissakataṃ, na "
"nimantanaṃ sādiyati, so na kumbhimukhā paṭiggaṇhāti, na kaḷopimukhā "
"paṭiggaṇhāti, na eḷakamantaraṃ, na daṇḍamantaraṃ, na musalamantaraṃ, na "
"dvinnaṃ bhuñjamānānaṃ, na gabbhiniyā, na pāyamānāya, na purisantaragatāya, "
"na saṅkittīsu, na yattha sā upaṭṭhito hoti, na yattha makkhikā "
"saṇḍasaṇḍacārinī, na macchaṃ, na maṃsaṃ, na suraṃ, na merayaṃ, na thusodakaṃ "
"pivati, so ekāgāriko vā hoti ekālopiko, dvāgāriko vā hoti dvālopiko, "
"sattāgāriko vā hoti sattālopiko, ekissāpi dattiyā yāpeti, dvīhipi dattīhi "
"yāpeti, sattahipi dattīhi yāpeti;"
msgstr ""
"“It’s when a mortifier goes naked, ignoring conventions. They lick their "
"hands, and don’t come or wait when asked. They don’t consent to food brought "
"to them, or food prepared on purpose for them, or an invitation for a meal. "
"They don’t receive anything from a pot or bowl; or from someone who keeps "
"sheep, or who has a weapon or a shovel in their home; or where a couple is "
"eating; or where there is a woman who is pregnant, breast-feeding, or who "
"has a man in her home; or where there’s a dog waiting or flies buzzing. They "
"accept no fish or meat or liquor or wine, and drink no beer. They go to just "
"one house for alms, taking just one mouthful, or two houses and two "
"mouthfuls, up to seven houses and seven mouthfuls. They feed on one saucer a "
"day, two saucers a day, up to seven saucers a day."

#. VAR: dvīhikampi → dvāhikaṃpi (bj, s1-3)
msgctxt "dn25:15.2"
msgid ""
"ekāhikampi āhāraṃ āhāreti, dvīhikampi āhāraṃ āhāreti, sattāhikampi āhāraṃ "
"āhāreti, iti evarūpaṃ addhamāsikampi pariyāyabhattabhojanānuyogamanuyutto "
"viharati."
msgstr ""
"They eat once a day, once every second day, up to once a week, and so on, "
"even up to once a fortnight. They live committed to the practice of eating "
"food at set intervals."

msgctxt "dn25:15.3"
msgid ""
"So sākabhakkho vā hoti, sāmākabhakkho vā hoti, nīvārabhakkho vā hoti, "
"daddulabhakkho vā hoti, haṭabhakkho vā hoti, kaṇabhakkho vā hoti, "
"ācāmabhakkho vā hoti, piññākabhakkho vā hoti, tiṇabhakkho vā hoti, "
"gomayabhakkho vā hoti;"
msgstr ""
"They eat herbs, millet, wild rice, poor rice, water lettuce, rice bran, scum "
"from boiling rice, sesame flour, grass, or cow dung. They survive on forest "
"roots and fruits, or eating fallen fruit."

msgctxt "dn25:15.4"
msgid "vanamūlaphalāhāro yāpeti pavattaphalabhojī."
msgstr "They feed on forest roots and fruits, or eating fallen fruit."

#. VAR: ubbhaṭṭhakopi → ubhaṭṭhakopi (s1-3) | ubbhaṭṭhikopi (mr)
#. VAR: ajinampi → ajinānipi (bj, s1-3, pts1, c1)
msgctxt "dn25:15.5"
msgid ""
"So sāṇānipi dhāreti, masāṇānipi dhāreti, chavadussānipi dhāreti, "
"paṃsukūlānipi dhāreti, tirīṭānipi dhāreti, ajinampi dhāreti, ajinakkhipampi "
"dhāreti, kusacīrampi dhāreti, vākacīrampi dhāreti, phalakacīrampi dhāreti, "
"kesakambalampi dhāreti, vāḷakambalampi dhāreti, ulūkapakkhampi dhāreti, "
"kesamassulocakopi hoti kesamassulocanānuyogamanuyutto, ubbhaṭṭhakopi hoti "
"āsanapaṭikkhitto, ukkuṭikopi hoti ukkuṭikappadhānamanuyutto, "
"kaṇṭakāpassayikopi hoti kaṇṭakāpassaye seyyaṃ kappeti, phalakaseyyampi "
"kappeti, thaṇḍilaseyyampi kappeti, ekapassayikopi hoti rajojalladharo, "
"abbhokāsikopi hoti yathāsanthatiko, vekaṭikopi hoti "
"vikaṭabhojanānuyogamanuyutto, apānakopi hoti apānakattamanuyutto, "
"sāyatatiyakampi udakorohanānuyogamanuyutto viharati."
msgstr ""
"They wear robes of sunn hemp, mixed hemp, corpse-wrapping cloth, rags, lodh "
"tree bark, antelope hide (whole or in strips), kusa grass, bark, wood-chips, "
"human hair, horse-tail hair, or owls’ wings. They tear out hair and beard, "
"committed to this practice. They constantly stand, refusing seats. They "
"squat, committed to persisting in the squatting position. They lie on a mat "
"of thorns, making a mat of thorns their bed. They make their bed on a plank, "
"or the bare ground. They lie only on one side. They wear dust and dirt. They "
"stay in the open air. They sleep wherever they lay their mat. They eat "
"unnatural things, committed to the practice of eating unnatural foods. They "
"don’t drink, committed to the practice of not drinking liquids. They’re "
"committed to the practice of immersion in water three times a day, including "
"the evening."

msgctxt "dn25:15.6"
msgid ""
"Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, nigrodha, yadi evaṃ sante tapojigucchā paripuṇṇā vā hoti "
"aparipuṇṇā vā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"What do you think, Nigrodha? If this is so, is the mortification in disgust "
"of sin completed, or incomplete?”"

msgctxt "dn25:15.7"
msgid ""
"“Addhā kho, bhante, evaṃ sante tapojigucchā paripuṇṇā hoti, no aparipuṇṇā”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Clearly, sir, if that is so the mortification in disgust of sin is "
"completed, not incomplete.”"

msgctxt "dn25:15.8"
msgid ""
"“Evaṃ paripuṇṇāyapi kho ahaṃ, nigrodha, tapojigucchāya anekavihite "
"upakkilese vadāmī”ti."
msgstr "“But even such a completed mortification has many flaws, I say.”"

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "dn25:16.1"
msgid "2.1. Upakkilesa"
msgstr "Flaws"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="12"></a><a class="wp" id="wp9"></a>
msgctxt "dn25:17.1"
msgid ""
"“Yathā kathaṃ pana, bhante, bhagavā evaṃ paripuṇṇāya tapojigucchāya "
"anekavihite upakkilese vadatī”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“But how does the Buddha say that even such a completed mortification has "
"many flaws?”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="13"></a>
msgctxt "dn25:18.1"
msgid ""
"“Idha, nigrodha, tapassī tapaṃ samādiyati, so tena tapasā attamano hoti "
"paripuṇṇasaṅkappo."
msgstr ""
"“Firstly, a mortifier undertakes a practice of mortification. They’re happy "
"with that, as they’ve got all they wished for."

msgctxt "dn25:18.2"
msgid ""
"Yampi, nigrodha, tapassī tapaṃ samādiyati, so tena tapasā attamano hoti "
"paripuṇṇasaṅkappo."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn25:18.3"
msgid "Ayampi kho, nigrodha, tapassino upakkileso hoti."
msgstr "This is a flaw in that mortifier."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="14"></a>
msgctxt "dn25:19.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, nigrodha, tapassī tapaṃ samādiyati, so tena tapasā "
"attānukkaṃseti paraṃ vambheti."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, a mortifier undertakes a practice of mortification. They "
"glorify themselves and put others down on account of that."

msgctxt "dn25:19.2"
msgid ""
"Yampi, nigrodha, tapassī tapaṃ samādiyati, so tena tapasā attānukkaṃseti "
"paraṃ vambheti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn25:19.3"
msgid "Ayampi kho, nigrodha, tapassino upakkileso hoti."
msgstr "This too is a flaw in that mortifier."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="15"></a><a class="pts" id="pts3.43"></a>
msgctxt "dn25:20.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, nigrodha, tapassī tapaṃ samādiyati, so tena tapasā majjati "
"mucchati pamādamāpajjati."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, a mortifier undertakes a practice of mortification. They become "
"indulgent and stupefied and fall into negligence on account of that."

msgctxt "dn25:20.2"
msgid ""
"Yampi, nigrodha, tapassī tapaṃ samādiyati, so tena tapasā majjati mucchati "
"pamādamāpajjati."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn25:20.3"
msgid "Ayampi kho, nigrodha, tapassino upakkileso hoti."
msgstr "This too is a flaw in that mortifier."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="16"></a><a class="wp" id="wp10"></a>
msgctxt "dn25:21.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, nigrodha, tapassī tapaṃ samādiyati, so tena tapasā "
"lābhasakkārasilokaṃ abhinibbatteti, so tena lābhasakkārasilokena attamano "
"hoti paripuṇṇasaṅkappo."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, a mortifier undertakes a practice of mortification. They "
"generate possessions, honor, and popularity through that mortification. They’"
"re happy with that, as they’ve got all they wished for."

msgctxt "dn25:21.2"
msgid ""
"Yampi, nigrodha, tapassī tapaṃ samādiyati, so tena tapasā "
"lābhasakkārasilokaṃ abhinibbatteti, so tena lābhasakkārasilokena attamano "
"hoti paripuṇṇasaṅkappo."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn25:21.3"
msgid "Ayampi kho, nigrodha, tapassino upakkileso hoti."
msgstr "This too is a flaw in that mortifier."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="17"></a>
msgctxt "dn25:22.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, nigrodha, tapassī tapaṃ samādiyati, so tena tapasā "
"lābhasakkārasilokaṃ abhinibbatteti, so tena lābhasakkārasilokena "
"attānukkaṃseti paraṃ vambheti."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, a mortifier undertakes a practice of mortification. They "
"generate possessions, honor, and popularity through that mortification. They "
"glorify themselves and put others down on account of that."

msgctxt "dn25:22.2"
msgid ""
"Yampi, nigrodha, tapassī tapaṃ samādiyati, so tena tapasā "
"lābhasakkārasilokaṃ abhinibbatteti, so tena lābhasakkārasilokena "
"attānukkaṃseti paraṃ vambheti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn25:22.3"
msgid "Ayampi kho, nigrodha, tapassino upakkileso hoti."
msgstr "This too is a flaw in that mortifier."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="18"></a>
msgctxt "dn25:23.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, nigrodha, tapassī tapaṃ samādiyati, so tena tapasā "
"lābhasakkārasilokaṃ abhinibbatteti, so tena lābhasakkārasilokena majjati "
"mucchati pamādamāpajjati."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, a mortifier undertakes a practice of mortification. They "
"generate possessions, honor, and popularity through that mortification. They "
"become indulgent and stupefied and fall into negligence on account of that."

msgctxt "dn25:23.2"
msgid ""
"Yampi, nigrodha, tapassī tapaṃ samādiyati, so tena tapasā "
"lābhasakkārasilokaṃ abhinibbatteti, so tena lābhasakkārasilokena majjati "
"mucchati pamādamāpajjati."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn25:23.3"
msgid "Ayampi kho, nigrodha, tapassino upakkileso hoti."
msgstr "This too is a flaw in that mortifier."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="19"></a>
msgctxt "dn25:24.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, nigrodha, tapassī bhojanesu vodāsaṃ āpajjati:"
msgstr "Furthermore, a mortifier becomes fussy about food, saying:"

msgctxt "dn25:24.2"
msgid "‘idaṃ me khamati, idaṃ me nakkhamatī’ti."
msgstr "‘This agrees with me, this doesn’t agree with me.’"

# Usually sapekkha is used in the sense of missing something, or longing for it when it's gone.
#. VAR: yañca → yaṃ hi (pts1)
msgctxt "dn25:24.3"
msgid "So yañca khvassa nakkhamati, taṃ sāpekkho pajahati."
msgstr "What doesn’t agree with them they reluctantly give up."

#. VAR: gadhito → gathito (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "dn25:24.4"
msgid ""
"Yaṃ panassa khamati, taṃ gadhito mucchito ajjhāpanno anādīnavadassāvī "
"anissaraṇapañño paribhuñjati …"
msgstr ""
"But what does agree with them they eat tied, stupefied, attached, blind to "
"the drawbacks, and not understanding the escape."

msgctxt "dn25:24.5"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn25:24.6"
msgid "ayampi kho, nigrodha, tapassino upakkileso hoti."
msgstr "This too is a flaw in that mortifier."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="20"></a><a class="pts" id="pts3.44"></a>
msgctxt "dn25:25.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, nigrodha, tapassī tapaṃ samādiyati "
"lābhasakkārasilokanikantihetu:"
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, a mortifier undertakes a practice of mortification out of  "
"longing for possessions, honor, and popularity, thinking:"

msgctxt "dn25:25.2"
msgid ""
"‘sakkarissanti maṃ rājāno rājamahāmattā khattiyā brāhmaṇā gahapatikā "
"titthiyā’ti …"
msgstr ""
"‘Kings, royal ministers, aristocrats, brahmins, householders, and sectarians "
"will honor me!’"

msgctxt "dn25:25.3"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn25:25.4"
msgid "ayampi kho, nigrodha, tapassino upakkileso hoti."
msgstr "This too is a flaw in that mortifier."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="21"></a><a class="wp" id="wp11"></a>
#. VAR: apasādetā → apasāretā (mr)
msgctxt "dn25:26.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, nigrodha, tapassī aññataraṃ samaṇaṃ vā brāhmaṇaṃ vā apasādetā "
"hoti:"
msgstr "Furthermore, a mortifier rebukes a certain ascetic or brahmin:"

#. VAR: sambahulājīvo → bahulājīvo (pts1)
msgctxt "dn25:26.2"
msgid "‘kiṃ panāyaṃ sambahulājīvo sabbaṃ sambhakkheti."
msgstr ""
"‘But what is this one doing, living in abundance! According to this ascetic’"
"s doctrine, everything—"

msgctxt "dn25:26.3"
msgid "Seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn25:26.4"
msgid ""
"mūlabījaṃ khandhabījaṃ phaḷubījaṃ aggabījaṃ bījabījameva pañcamaṃ, "
"asanivicakkaṃ dantakūṭaṃ, samaṇappavādenā’ti …"
msgstr ""
"plants propagated from roots, stems, cuttings, or joints; and those from "
"regular seeds as the fifth—is crunched together like the thunder of a tooth-"
"hammer!’"

msgctxt "dn25:26.5"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn25:26.6"
msgid "ayampi kho, nigrodha, tapassino upakkileso hoti."
msgstr "This too is a flaw in that mortifier."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="22"></a>
msgctxt "dn25:27.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, nigrodha, tapassī passati aññataraṃ samaṇaṃ vā brāhmaṇaṃ vā "
"kulesu sakkariyamānaṃ garukariyamānaṃ māniyamānaṃ pūjiyamānaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, a mortifier sees a certain ascetic or brahmin being honored, "
"respected, esteemed, and venerated among respectable families."

msgctxt "dn25:27.2"
msgid "Disvā tassa evaṃ hoti:"
msgstr "They think:"

msgctxt "dn25:27.3"
msgid ""
"‘imañhi nāma sambahulājīvaṃ kulesu sakkaronti garuṃ karonti mānenti pūjenti."
msgstr ""
"‘This one, who lives in abundance, is honored, respected, esteemed, and "
"venerated among respectable families."

msgctxt "dn25:27.4"
msgid ""
"Maṃ pana tapassiṃ lūkhājīviṃ kulesu na sakkaronti na garuṃ karonti na "
"mānenti na pūjentī’ti, iti so issāmacchariyaṃ kulesu uppādetā hoti …"
msgstr ""
"But I, a self-mortifier who lives rough, am not honored, respected, "
"esteemed, and venerated among respectable families.’ Thus they give rise to "
"envy and jealousy regarding families."

msgctxt "dn25:27.5"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn25:27.6"
msgid "ayampi kho, nigrodha, tapassino upakkileso hoti."
msgstr "This too is a flaw in that mortifier."

# Note that while PTS dict derives nisādī from sad and has "lying down", comm has "dassanaṭṭhāne nisīdati". This is supported by the other uses at ja538#37 and tha-ap407#45 (vl. nisīdetvana)
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="23"></a>
msgctxt "dn25:28.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, nigrodha, tapassī āpāthakanisādī hoti …"
msgstr "Furthermore, a mortifier sits meditation only when people can see them."

msgctxt "dn25:28.2"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn25:28.3"
msgid "ayampi kho, nigrodha, tapassino upakkileso hoti."
msgstr "This too is a flaw in that mortifier."

# As noted by MW, comm here says "adassayamānoti ettha a-kāro nipātamattaṃ, dassayamānoti attho". But this seems odd. Tika says ‘‘Ādassayamāno’’ti vā pāṭho. Again, this seems odd. If the first explanation is good, why need another? And if it is a genuine reading, it does not seem to be attested. Further, ādassana doesn't seem to be attested as a genuine Pali term. 
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="24"></a>
msgctxt "dn25:29.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, nigrodha, tapassī attānaṃ adassayamāno kulesu carati:"
msgstr "Furthermore, a mortifier sneaks about among families, thinking:"

msgctxt "dn25:29.2"
msgid "‘idampi me tapasmiṃ idampi me tapasmin’ti …"
msgstr "‘This is part of my mortification; this is part of my mortification.’"

msgctxt "dn25:29.3"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn25:29.4"
msgid "ayampi kho, nigrodha, tapassino upakkileso hoti."
msgstr "This too is a flaw in that mortifier."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="25"></a><a class="pts" id="pts3.45"></a>
msgctxt "dn25:30.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, nigrodha, tapassī kiñcideva paṭicchannaṃ sevati."
msgstr "Furthermore, a mortifier sometimes behaves in an underhand manner."

# Note that comm applies this to views "Kiñcidevāti kiñci vajjaṃ diṭṭhigataṃ vā", but earlier in the sutta "idaṃ me khamati, idaṃ me nakkhamatī’ti." is applied to preferences regarding food. 
msgctxt "dn25:30.2"
msgid "So ‘khamati te idan’ti puṭṭho samāno akkhamamānaṃ āha:"
msgstr ""
"When asked whether something agrees with them, they say it does, even though "
"it doesn’t."

msgctxt "dn25:30.3"
msgid "‘khamatī’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn25:30.4"
msgid "Khamamānaṃ āha:"
msgstr "Or they say it doesn’t, even though it does."

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn25:30.5"
msgid "‘nakkhamatī’ti."
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn25:30.6"
msgid "Iti so sampajānamusā bhāsitā hoti …"
msgstr "Thus they tell a deliberate lie."

msgctxt "dn25:30.7"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn25:30.8"
msgid "ayampi kho, nigrodha, tapassino upakkileso hoti."
msgstr "This too is a flaw in that mortifier."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="26"></a><a class="wp" id="wp12"></a>
msgctxt "dn25:31.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, nigrodha, tapassī tathāgatassa vā tathāgatasāvakassa vā "
"dhammaṃ desentassa santaṃyeva pariyāyaṃ anuññeyyaṃ nānujānāti …"
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, a mortifier disagrees with the way that the Realized One or "
"their disciple teaches Dhamma, even when they make a valid point."

msgctxt "dn25:31.2"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn25:31.3"
msgid "ayampi kho, nigrodha, tapassino upakkileso hoti."
msgstr "This too is a flaw in that mortifier."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="27"></a>
msgctxt "dn25:32.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, nigrodha, tapassī kodhano hoti upanāhī."
msgstr "Furthermore, a mortifier is angry and hostile …"

msgctxt "dn25:32.2"
msgid "Yampi, nigrodha, tapassī kodhano hoti upanāhī."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn25:32.3"
msgid "Ayampi kho, nigrodha, tapassino upakkileso hoti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="28"></a>
#. VAR: paḷāsī → palāsī (s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "dn25:33.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, nigrodha, tapassī makkhī hoti paḷāsī …"
msgstr "offensive and insolent …"

msgctxt "dn25:33.2"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn25:33.3"
msgid "issukī hoti maccharī …"
msgstr "envious and stingy …"

msgctxt "dn25:33.4"
msgid "saṭho hoti māyāvī …"
msgstr "manipulative and deceitful …"

msgctxt "dn25:33.5"
msgid "thaddho hoti atimānī …"
msgstr "obstinate and vain …"

msgctxt "dn25:33.6"
msgid "pāpiccho hoti pāpikānaṃ icchānaṃ vasaṃ gato …"
msgstr "they have wicked desires, falling under the sway of wicked desires …"

msgctxt "dn25:33.7"
msgid "micchādiṭṭhiko hoti antaggāhikāya diṭṭhiyā samannāgato …"
msgstr "they have wrong view, being attached to an extremist view …"

msgctxt "dn25:33.8"
msgid "sandiṭṭhiparāmāsī hoti ādhānaggāhī duppaṭinissaggī."
msgstr ""
"they’re attached to their own views, holding them tight, and refusing to let "
"go."

msgctxt "dn25:33.9"
msgid ""
"Yampi, nigrodha, tapassī sandiṭṭhiparāmāsī hoti ādhānaggāhī duppaṭinissaggī."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn25:33.10"
msgid "Ayampi kho, nigrodha, tapassino upakkileso hoti."
msgstr "This too is a flaw in that mortifier."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="29"></a>
#. VAR: upakkilesā → upakkilesā hoti (mr)
#. VAR: tapojigucchā → tapojigucchāya (?)
msgctxt "dn25:34.1"
msgid ""
"Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, nigrodha, yadime tapojigucchā upakkilesā vā anupakkilesā "
"vā”ti?"
msgstr "What do you think, Nigrodha? Are such mortifications flawed or not?”"

msgctxt "dn25:34.2"
msgid "“Addhā kho ime, bhante, tapojigucchā upakkilesā, no anupakkilesā."
msgstr "“Clearly, sir, they’re flawed. "

msgctxt "dn25:34.3"
msgid ""
"Ṭhānaṃ kho panetaṃ, bhante, vijjati yaṃ idhekacco tapassī sabbeheva imehi "
"upakkilesehi samannāgato assa;"
msgstr "It’s possible that a mortifier might have all of these flaws,"

msgctxt "dn25:34.4"
msgid "ko pana vādo aññataraññatarenā”ti."
msgstr "not to speak of one or other of them.”"

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "dn25:35.1"
msgid "2.2. Parisuddhapapaṭikappattakathā"
msgstr "On Reaching the Shoots"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="30"></a><a class="wp" id="wp13"></a><a class="pts"
#. id="pts3.46"></a>
msgctxt "dn25:36.1"
msgid ""
"“Idha, nigrodha, tapassī tapaṃ samādiyati, so tena tapasā na attamano hoti "
"na paripuṇṇasaṅkappo."
msgstr ""
"“Firstly, Nigrodha, a mortifier undertakes a practice of mortification. But "
"they’re not happy with that, as they still haven’t got all they wished for."

msgctxt "dn25:36.2"
msgid ""
"Yampi, nigrodha, tapassī tapaṃ samādiyati, so tena tapasā na attamano hoti "
"na paripuṇṇasaṅkappo."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn25:36.3"
msgid "Evaṃ so tasmiṃ ṭhāne parisuddho hoti."
msgstr "So they’re pure on that point."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="31"></a>
msgctxt "dn25:37.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, nigrodha, tapassī tapaṃ samādiyati, so tena tapasā na "
"attānukkaṃseti na paraṃ vambheti …"
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, a mortifier undertakes a practice of mortification. They don’t "
"glorify themselves or put others down on account of that."

msgctxt "dn25:37.2"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn25:37.3"
msgid "evaṃ so tasmiṃ ṭhāne parisuddho hoti."
msgstr "So they’re pure on that point."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="32"></a>
msgctxt "dn25:38.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, nigrodha, tapassī tapaṃ samādiyati, so tena tapasā na majjati "
"na mucchati na pamādamāpajjati …"
msgstr "They don’t become indulgent …"

msgctxt "dn25:38.2"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn25:38.3"
msgid "evaṃ so tasmiṃ ṭhāne parisuddho hoti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="33"></a>
msgctxt "dn25:39.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, nigrodha, tapassī tapaṃ samādiyati, so tena tapasā "
"lābhasakkārasilokaṃ abhinibbatteti, so tena lābhasakkārasilokena na attamano "
"hoti na paripuṇṇasaṅkappo …"
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, a mortifier undertakes a practice of mortification. They "
"generate possessions, honor, and popularity through that mortification. They’"
"re not happy with that, as they still haven’t got all they wished for …"

msgctxt "dn25:39.2"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn25:39.3"
msgid "evaṃ so tasmiṃ ṭhāne parisuddho hoti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="34"></a>
msgctxt "dn25:40.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, nigrodha, tapassī tapaṃ samādiyati, so tena tapasā "
"lābhasakkārasilokaṃ abhinibbatteti, so tena lābhasakkārasilokena na "
"attānukkaṃseti na paraṃ vambheti …"
msgstr ""
"They don’t glorify themselves and put others down on account of possessions, "
"honor, and popularity …"

msgctxt "dn25:40.2"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn25:40.3"
msgid "evaṃ so tasmiṃ ṭhāne parisuddho hoti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="35"></a>
msgctxt "dn25:41.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, nigrodha, tapassī tapaṃ samādiyati, so tena tapasā "
"lābhasakkārasilokaṃ abhinibbatteti, so tena lābhasakkārasilokena na majjati "
"na mucchati na pamādamāpajjati …"
msgstr "They don’t become indulgent because of it …"

msgctxt "dn25:41.2"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn25:41.3"
msgid "evaṃ so tasmiṃ ṭhāne parisuddho hoti."
msgstr "So they’re pure on that point."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="36"></a>
msgctxt "dn25:42.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, nigrodha, tapassī bhojanesu na vodāsaṃ āpajjati:"
msgstr "Furthermore, a mortifier doesn’t become fussy about food, saying:"

msgctxt "dn25:42.2"
msgid "‘idaṃ me khamati, idaṃ me nakkhamatī’ti."
msgstr "‘This agrees with me, this doesn’t agree with me.’"

msgctxt "dn25:42.3"
msgid "So yañca khvassa nakkhamati, taṃ anapekkho pajahati."
msgstr "What doesn’t agree with them they readily give up."

msgctxt "dn25:42.4"
msgid ""
"Yaṃ panassa khamati, taṃ agadhito amucchito anajjhāpanno ādīnavadassāvī "
"nissaraṇapañño paribhuñjati …"
msgstr ""
"But what does agree with them they eat without being tied, stupefied, "
"attached, blind to the drawbacks, and not understanding the escape."

msgctxt "dn25:42.5"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn25:42.6"
msgid "evaṃ so tasmiṃ ṭhāne parisuddho hoti."
msgstr "So they’re pure on that point."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="37"></a>
msgctxt "dn25:43.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, nigrodha, tapassī na tapaṃ samādiyati "
"lābhasakkārasilokanikantihetu:"
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, a mortifier doesn’t undertake a practice of mortification out "
"of longing for possessions, honor, and popularity …"

msgctxt "dn25:43.2"
msgid ""
"‘sakkarissanti maṃ rājāno rājamahāmattā khattiyā brāhmaṇā gahapatikā "
"titthiyā’ti …"
msgstr ""
"‘Kings, royal ministers, aristocrats, brahmins, householders, and sectarians "
"will honor me!’"

msgctxt "dn25:43.3"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn25:43.4"
msgid "evaṃ so tasmiṃ ṭhāne parisuddho hoti."
msgstr "So they’re pure on that point."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="38"></a><a class="pts" id="pts3.47"></a>
msgctxt "dn25:44.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, nigrodha, tapassī aññataraṃ samaṇaṃ vā brāhmaṇaṃ vā nāpasādetā "
"hoti:"
msgstr "Furthermore, a mortifier doesn’t rebuke a certain ascetic or brahmin:"

msgctxt "dn25:44.2"
msgid "‘kiṃ panāyaṃ sambahulājīvo sabbaṃ sambhakkheti."
msgstr ""
"‘But what is this one doing, living in abundance! According to this ascetic’"
"s doctrine, everything—"

msgctxt "dn25:44.3"
msgid "Seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn25:44.4"
msgid ""
"mūlabījaṃ khandhabījaṃ phaḷubījaṃ aggabījaṃ bījabījameva pañcamaṃ, "
"asanivicakkaṃ dantakūṭaṃ, samaṇappavādenā’ti …"
msgstr ""
"plants propagated from roots, stems, cuttings, or joints; and those from "
"regular seeds as the fifth—is crunched together like the thunder of a tooth-"
"hammer!’"

msgctxt "dn25:44.5"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn25:44.6"
msgid "evaṃ so tasmiṃ ṭhāne parisuddho hoti."
msgstr "So they’re pure on that point."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="39"></a><a class="wp" id="wp14"></a>
msgctxt "dn25:45.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, nigrodha, tapassī passati aññataraṃ samaṇaṃ vā brāhmaṇaṃ vā "
"kulesu sakkariyamānaṃ garu kariyamānaṃ māniyamānaṃ pūjiyamānaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, a mortifier sees a certain ascetic or brahmin being honored, "
"respected, esteemed, and venerated among respectable families."

msgctxt "dn25:45.2"
msgid "Disvā tassa na evaṃ hoti:"
msgstr "It never occurs to them:"

msgctxt "dn25:45.3"
msgid ""
"‘imañhi nāma sambahulājīvaṃ kulesu sakkaronti garuṃ karonti mānenti pūjenti."
msgstr ""
"‘This one, who lives in abundance, is honored, respected, esteemed, and "
"venerated among respectable families."

msgctxt "dn25:45.4"
msgid ""
"Maṃ pana tapassiṃ lūkhājīviṃ kulesu na sakkaronti na garuṃ karonti na "
"mānenti na pūjentī’ti, iti so issāmacchariyaṃ kulesu nuppādetā hoti …"
msgstr ""
"But I, a self-mortifier who lives rough, am not honored, respected, "
"esteemed, and venerated among respectable families.’ Thus they don’t give "
"rise to envy and jealousy regarding families."

msgctxt "dn25:45.5"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn25:45.6"
msgid "evaṃ so tasmiṃ ṭhāne parisuddho hoti."
msgstr "So they’re pure on that point."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="40"></a>
msgctxt "dn25:46.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, nigrodha, tapassī na āpāthakanisādī hoti …"
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, a mortifier doesn’t sit meditation only when people can see "
"them."

msgctxt "dn25:46.2"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn25:46.3"
msgid "evaṃ so tasmiṃ ṭhāne parisuddho hoti."
msgstr "So they’re pure on that point."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="41"></a>
msgctxt "dn25:47.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, nigrodha, tapassī na attānaṃ adassayamāno kulesu carati:"
msgstr "Furthermore, a mortifier doesn’t sneak about among families, thinking:"

msgctxt "dn25:47.2"
msgid "‘idampi me tapasmiṃ, idampi me tapasmin’ti …"
msgstr "‘This is part of my mortification; this is part of my mortification.’"

msgctxt "dn25:47.3"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn25:47.4"
msgid "evaṃ so tasmiṃ ṭhāne parisuddho hoti."
msgstr "So they’re pure on that point."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="42"></a>
msgctxt "dn25:48.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, nigrodha, tapassī na kiñcideva paṭicchannaṃ sevati, so:"
msgstr "Furthermore, a mortifier never behaves in an underhand manner."

msgctxt "dn25:48.2"
msgid "‘khamati te idan’ti puṭṭho samāno akkhamamānaṃ āha:"
msgstr ""
"When asked whether something agrees with them, they say it doesn’t when it "
"doesn’t."

msgctxt "dn25:48.3"
msgid "‘nakkhamatī’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn25:48.4"
msgid "Khamamānaṃ āha:"
msgstr "Or they say it does when it does."

msgctxt "dn25:48.5"
msgid "‘khamatī’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn25:48.6"
msgid "Iti so sampajānamusā na bhāsitā hoti …"
msgstr "Thus they don’t tell a deliberate lie."

msgctxt "dn25:48.7"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn25:48.8"
msgid "evaṃ so tasmiṃ ṭhāne parisuddho hoti."
msgstr "So they’re pure on that point."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="43"></a><a class="wp" id="wp15"></a>
msgctxt "dn25:49.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, nigrodha, tapassī tathāgatassa vā tathāgatasāvakassa vā "
"dhammaṃ desentassa santaṃyeva pariyāyaṃ anuññeyyaṃ anujānāti …"
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, a mortifier agrees with the way that the Realized One or their "
"disciple teaches Dhamma when they make a valid point."

msgctxt "dn25:49.2"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn25:49.3"
msgid "evaṃ so tasmiṃ ṭhāne parisuddho hoti."
msgstr "So they’re pure on that point."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="44"></a>
msgctxt "dn25:50.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, nigrodha, tapassī akkodhano hoti anupanāhī."
msgstr "Furthermore, a mortifier is not angry and hostile …"

msgctxt "dn25:50.2"
msgid ""
"Yampi, nigrodha, tapassī akkodhano hoti anupanāhī evaṃ so tasmiṃ ṭhāne "
"parisuddho hoti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="45"></a><a class="pts" id="pts3.48"></a>
msgctxt "dn25:51.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, nigrodha, tapassī amakkhī hoti apaḷāsī …"
msgstr "offensive and insolent …"

msgctxt "dn25:51.2"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn25:51.3"
msgid "anissukī hoti amaccharī …"
msgstr "envious and stingy …"

msgctxt "dn25:51.4"
msgid "asaṭho hoti amāyāvī …"
msgstr "manipulative and deceitful …"

msgctxt "dn25:51.5"
msgid "atthaddho hoti anatimānī …"
msgstr "obstinate and vain …"

msgctxt "dn25:51.6"
msgid "na pāpiccho hoti na pāpikānaṃ icchānaṃ vasaṃ gato …"
msgstr "they don’t have wicked desires …"

msgctxt "dn25:51.7"
msgid "na micchādiṭṭhiko hoti na antaggāhikāya diṭṭhiyā samannāgato …"
msgstr "and wrong view …"

msgctxt "dn25:51.8"
msgid "na sandiṭṭhiparāmāsī hoti na ādhānaggāhī suppaṭinissaggī."
msgstr ""
"they’re not attached to their own views, holding them tight, and refusing to "
"let go."

msgctxt "dn25:51.9"
msgid ""
"Yampi, nigrodha, tapassī na sandiṭṭhiparāmāsī hoti na ādhānaggāhī "
"suppaṭinissaggī."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn25:51.10"
msgid "Evaṃ so tasmiṃ ṭhāne parisuddho hoti."
msgstr "So they’re pure on that point."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="46"></a>
msgctxt "dn25:52.1"
msgid ""
"Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, nigrodha, yadi evaṃ sante tapojigucchā parisuddhā vā hoti "
"aparisuddhā vā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"What do you think, Nigrodha? If this is so, is the mortification in disgust "
"of sin purified or not?”"

msgctxt "dn25:52.2"
msgid ""
"“Addhā kho, bhante, evaṃ sante tapojigucchā parisuddhā hoti no aparisuddhā, "
"aggappattā ca sārappattā cā”ti."
msgstr "“Clearly, sir, it is purified. It has reached the peak and the pith.”"

msgctxt "dn25:52.3"
msgid ""
"“Na kho, nigrodha, ettāvatā tapojigucchā aggappattā ca hoti sārappattā ca;"
msgstr ""
"“No, Nigrodha, at this point the mortification in disgust of sin has not yet "
"reached the peak and the pith."

#. VAR: papaṭikappattā → pappaṭikapattā (s1-3, mr) | papaṭikapattā (pts1)
msgctxt "dn25:52.4"
msgid "api ca kho papaṭikappattā hotī”ti."
msgstr "Rather, it has only reached the shoots.”"

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "dn25:53.1"
msgid "2.3. Parisuddhatacappattakathā"
msgstr "On Reaching the Bark"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="47"></a><a class="wp" id="wp16"></a>
#. VAR: aggappattā ca hoti sārappattā ca → aggappattā ca sārappattā ca hoti
#. (s1-3, c1)
msgctxt "dn25:54.1"
msgid "“Kittāvatā pana, bhante, tapojigucchā aggappattā ca hoti sārappattā ca?"
msgstr ""
"“But at what point, sir, does the mortification in disgust of sin reach the "
"peak and the pith?"

msgctxt "dn25:54.2"
msgid ""
"Sādhu me, bhante, bhagavā tapojigucchāya aggaññeva pāpetu, sāraññeva "
"pāpetū”ti."
msgstr "Please help me reach the peak and the pith!”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="48"></a><a class="pts" id="pts3.49"></a>
msgctxt "dn25:55.1"
msgid "“Idha, nigrodha, tapassī cātuyāmasaṃvarasaṃvuto hoti."
msgstr ""
"“Nigrodha, take a mortifier who is restrained in the fourfold restraint."

msgctxt "dn25:55.2"
msgid "Kathañca, nigrodha, tapassī cātuyāmasaṃvarasaṃvuto hoti?"
msgstr "And how is a mortifier restrained in the fourfold restraint?"

# Cp AN 3.163
#. VAR: atipāteti → atipāpeti (si, pts1, mr)
msgctxt "dn25:55.3"
msgid ""
"Idha, nigrodha, tapassī na pāṇaṃ atipāteti, na pāṇaṃ atipātayati, na "
"pāṇamatipātayato samanuñño hoti."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mortifier doesn’t kill living creatures, doesn’t get others to "
"kill, and doesn’t approve of killing."

msgctxt "dn25:55.4"
msgid ""
"Na adinnaṃ ādiyati, na adinnaṃ ādiyāpeti, na adinnaṃ ādiyato samanuñño hoti."
msgstr "They don’t steal, get others to steal, or approve of stealing."

msgctxt "dn25:55.5"
msgid "Na musā bhaṇati, na musā bhaṇāpeti, na musā bhaṇato samanuñño hoti."
msgstr "They don’t lie, get others to lie, or approve of lying."

# This term is unique. Comm has "Na bhāvitamāsīsatīti bhāvitaṃ nāma tesaṃ saññāya pañca kāmaguṇā, te na āsīsati na sevatīti attho."
msgctxt "dn25:55.6"
msgid ""
"Na bhāvitamāsīsati, na bhāvitamāsīsāpeti, na bhāvitamāsīsato samanuñño hoti."
msgstr ""
"They don’t expect rewards from their practice, they don’t lead other others "
"to expect rewards, and they don’t approve of expecting rewards."

msgctxt "dn25:55.7"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, nigrodha, tapassī cātuyāmasaṃvarasaṃvuto hoti."
msgstr "That’s how a mortifier is restrained in the fourfold restraint."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="49"></a>
msgctxt "dn25:56.1"
msgid ""
"Yato kho, nigrodha, tapassī cātuyāmasaṃvarasaṃvuto hoti, aduṃ cassa hoti "
"tapassitāya."
msgstr ""
"When a mortifier has the fourfold restraint, that is their mortification."

msgctxt "dn25:56.2"
msgid "So abhiharati no hīnāyāvattati."
msgstr "They step forward, not falling back."

msgctxt "dn25:56.3"
msgid ""
"So vivittaṃ senāsanaṃ bhajati araññaṃ rukkhamūlaṃ pabbataṃ kandaraṃ "
"giriguhaṃ susānaṃ vanapatthaṃ abbhokāsaṃ palālapuñjaṃ."
msgstr ""
"They frequent a secluded lodging—a wilderness, the root of a tree, a hill, a "
"ravine, a mountain cave, a charnel ground, a forest, the open air, a heap of "
"straw."

msgctxt "dn25:56.4"
msgid ""
"So pacchābhattaṃ piṇḍapātapaṭikkanto nisīdati pallaṅkaṃ ābhujitvā ujuṃ kāyaṃ "
"paṇidhāya parimukhaṃ satiṃ upaṭṭhapetvā."
msgstr ""
"After the meal, they return from alms-round, sit down in the meditation "
"posture with their body erect, and establish mindfulness right there."

msgctxt "dn25:56.5"
msgid ""
"So abhijjhaṃ loke pahāya vigatābhijjhena cetasā viharati, abhijjhāya cittaṃ "
"parisodheti."
msgstr ""
"Giving up desire for the world, they meditate with a heart rid of desire, "
"cleansing the mind of desire."

msgctxt "dn25:56.6"
msgid ""
"Byāpādappadosaṃ pahāya abyāpannacitto viharati sabbapāṇabhūtahitānukampī, "
"byāpādappadosā cittaṃ parisodheti."
msgstr ""
"Giving up ill will and malevolence, they meditate with a mind rid of ill "
"will, full of compassion for all creatures, cleansing the mind of ill will."

#. VAR: Thinamiddhaṃ → thīnamiddhaṃ (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "dn25:56.7"
msgid ""
"Thinamiddhaṃ pahāya vigatathinamiddho viharati ālokasaññī sato sampajāno, "
"thinamiddhā cittaṃ parisodheti."
msgstr ""
"Giving up dullness and drowsiness, they meditate with a mind rid of dullness "
"and drowsiness, perceiving light, mindful and aware, cleansing the mind of "
"dullness and drowsiness."

msgctxt "dn25:56.8"
msgid ""
"Uddhaccakukkuccaṃ pahāya anuddhato viharati ajjhattaṃ vūpasantacitto, "
"uddhaccakukkuccā cittaṃ parisodheti."
msgstr ""
"Giving up restlessness and remorse, they meditate without restlessness, "
"their mind peaceful inside, cleansing the mind of restlessness and remorse."

msgctxt "dn25:56.9"
msgid ""
"Vicikicchaṃ pahāya tiṇṇavicikiccho viharati akathaṃkathī kusalesu dhammesu, "
"vicikicchāya cittaṃ parisodheti."
msgstr ""
"Giving up doubt, they meditate having gone beyond doubt, not undecided about "
"wholesome qualities, cleansing the mind of doubt."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="50"></a><a class="wp" id="wp17"></a><a class="pts"
#. id="pts3.50"></a>
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn25:57.1"
msgid ""
"So ime pañca nīvaraṇe pahāya cetaso upakkilese paññāya dubbalīkaraṇe "
"mettāsahagatena cetasā ekaṃ disaṃ pharitvā viharati."
msgstr ""
"They give up these five hindrances, corruptions of the heart that weaken "
"wisdom. "

msgctxt "dn25:57.2"
msgid "Tathā dutiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Then they meditate spreading a heart full of love to one direction, and to "
"the second, and to the third, and to the fourth. In the same way above, "
"below, across, everywhere, all around, they spread a heart full of love to "
"the whole world—abundant, expansive, limitless, free of enmity and ill will."

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn25:57.3"
msgid "Tathā tatiyaṃ."
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn25:57.4"
msgid "Tathā catutthaṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn25:57.5"
msgid ""
"Iti uddhamadho tiriyaṃ sabbadhi sabbattatāya sabbāvantaṃ lokaṃ "
"mettāsahagatena cetasā vipulena mahaggatena appamāṇena averena abyāpajjena "
"pharitvā viharati."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn25:57.6"
msgid "Karuṇāsahagatena cetasā …"
msgstr "They meditate spreading a heart full of compassion …"

msgctxt "dn25:57.7"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn25:57.8"
msgid "muditāsahagatena cetasā …"
msgstr "They meditate spreading a heart full of rejoicing …"

msgctxt "dn25:57.9"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn25:57.10"
msgid "upekkhāsahagatena cetasā ekaṃ disaṃ pharitvā viharati."
msgstr ""
"They meditate spreading a heart full of equanimity to one direction, and to "
"the second, and to the third, and to the fourth. In the same way above, "
"below, across, everywhere, all around, they spread a heart full of "
"equanimity to the whole world—abundant, expansive, limitless, free of enmity "
"and ill will."

msgctxt "dn25:57.11"
msgid "Tathā dutiyaṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn25:57.12"
msgid "Tathā tatiyaṃ."
msgstr ""

