"aggappattā ca sārappattā cā”ti."
msgstr "“Clearly, sir, it is purified. It has reached the peak and the pith.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="58"></a>
#. VAR: kho, nigrodha → iti nigrodha (s1-3) | atha taṃ nigrodha (km)
msgctxt "dn25:67.1"
msgid "“Ettāvatā kho, nigrodha, tapojigucchā aggappattā ca hoti sārappattā ca."
msgstr ""
"“Nigrodha, at this point the mortification in disgust of sin has reached the "
"peak and the pith."

msgctxt "dn25:67.2"
msgid "Iti kho, nigrodha, yaṃ maṃ tvaṃ avacāsi:"
msgstr "Nigrodha, remember you said this to me:"

msgctxt "dn25:67.3"
msgid ""
"‘ko nāma so, bhante, bhagavato dhammo, yena bhagavā sāvake vineti, yena "
"bhagavatā sāvakā vinītā assāsappattā paṭijānanti ajjhāsayaṃ "
"ādibrahmacariyan’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Sir, what teaching do you use to guide your disciples, through which they "
"claim solace in the fundamental purpose of the spiritual life?’"

msgctxt "dn25:67.4"
msgid ""
"Iti kho taṃ, nigrodha, ṭhānaṃ uttaritarañca paṇītatarañca, yenāhaṃ sāvake "
"vinemi, yena mayā sāvakā vinītā assāsappattā paṭijānanti ajjhāsayaṃ "
"ādibrahmacariyan”ti."
msgstr ""
"Well, there is something better and finer than this. That’s what I use to "
"use to guide my disciples, through which they claim solace in the "
"fundamental purpose of the spiritual life.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="59"></a>
msgctxt "dn25:68.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, te paribbājakā unnādino uccāsaddamahāsaddā ahesuṃ:"
msgstr "When he said this, those wanderers made an uproar:"

msgctxt "dn25:68.2"
msgid ""
"“ettha mayaṃ anassāma sācariyakā, na mayaṃ ito bhiyyo uttaritaraṃ "
"pajānāmā”ti."
msgstr ""
"“In that case, we’re lost, and so is our tradition! We don’t know anything "
"better or finer than that!”"

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn25:69.1"
msgid "4. Nigrodhassapajjhāyana"
msgstr "Nigrodha Feels Depressed"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="60"></a><a class="wp" id="wp20"></a><a class="pts"
#. id="pts3.53"></a>
msgctxt "dn25:70.1"
msgid "Yadā aññāsi sandhāno gahapati:"
msgstr "Then the householder Sandhāna realized:"

msgctxt "dn25:70.2"
msgid ""
"“aññadatthu kho dānime aññatitthiyā paribbājakā bhagavato bhāsitaṃ "
"sussūsanti, sotaṃ odahanti, aññācittaṃ upaṭṭhāpentī”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Obviously, now these wanderers want to listen to what the Buddha says. They’"
"re paying attention and applying their minds to understand!”"

#. VAR: Atha → atha naṃ (mr)
msgctxt "dn25:70.3"
msgid "Atha nigrodhaṃ paribbājakaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "So he said to the wanderer Nigrodha:"

msgctxt "dn25:70.4"
msgid "“iti kho, bhante nigrodha, yaṃ maṃ tvaṃ avacāsi:"
msgstr "“Nigrodha, remember you said this to me:"

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn25:70.5"
msgid ""
"‘yagghe, gahapati, jāneyyāsi, kena samaṇo gotamo saddhiṃ sallapati, kena "
"sākacchaṃ samāpajjati, kena paññāveyyattiyaṃ samāpajjati, suññāgārahatā "
"samaṇassa gotamassa paññā, aparisāvacaro samaṇo gotamo nālaṃ sallāpāya, so "
"antamantāneva sevati;"
msgstr ""
"‘Surely, householder, you should know better! With whom does the ascetic "
"Gotama converse? With whom does he engage in discussion? With whom does he "
"achieve proficiency in wisdom? Staying in empty huts has destroyed the "
"ascetic Gotama’s wisdom. Not frequenting assemblies, he is unable to hold a "
"discussion. He just lurks on the periphery."

msgctxt "dn25:70.6"
msgid "seyyathāpi nāma gokāṇā pariyantacārinī antamantāneva sevati."
msgstr ""
"He’s just like the nilgai antelope, circling around and lurking on the "
"periphery."

msgctxt "dn25:70.7"
msgid ""
"Evameva suññāgārahatā samaṇassa gotamassa paññā, aparisāvacaro samaṇo gotamo "
"nālaṃ sallāpāya;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn25:70.8"
msgid "so antamantāneva sevati;"
msgstr ""

#. VAR: iṅgha → iṅgha ca (bj, c1)
msgctxt "dn25:70.9"
msgid ""
"iṅgha, gahapati, samaṇo gotamo imaṃ parisaṃ āgaccheyya, ekapañheneva naṃ "
"saṃsādeyyāma, tucchakumbhīva naṃ maññe orodheyyāmā’ti."
msgstr ""
"Please, householder, let the ascetic Gotama come to this assembly. I’ll sink "
"him with just one question! I’ll roll him over and wrap him up like an empty "
"pot!’"

msgctxt "dn25:70.10"
msgid ""
"Ayaṃ kho so, bhante, bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho idhānuppatto, "
"aparisāvacaraṃ pana naṃ karotha, gokāṇaṃ pariyantacāriniṃ karotha, "
"ekapañheneva naṃ saṃsādetha, tucchakumbhīva naṃ orodhethā”ti."
msgstr ""
"Now the Blessed One, perfected and fully awakened, has arrived here. Why don’"
"t you send him out of the assembly to the periphery like a nilgai antelope? "
"Why don’t you sink him with just one question? Why don’t you roll him over "
"and wrap him up like an empty pot?”"

msgctxt "dn25:70.11"
msgid ""
"Evaṃ vutte, nigrodho paribbājako tuṇhībhūto maṅkubhūto pattakkhandho "
"adhomukho pajjhāyanto appaṭibhāno nisīdi."
msgstr ""
"When he said this, Nigrodha sat silent, embarrassed, shoulders drooping, "
"downcast, depressed, with nothing to say."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="61"></a><a class="wp" id="wp21"></a><a class="pts"
#. id="pts3.54"></a>
msgctxt "dn25:71.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā nigrodhaṃ paribbājakaṃ tuṇhībhūtaṃ maṅkubhūtaṃ "
"pattakkhandhaṃ adhomukhaṃ pajjhāyantaṃ appaṭibhānaṃ viditvā nigrodhaṃ "
"paribbājakaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "Knowing this, the Buddha said to him:"

msgctxt "dn25:71.2"
msgid "“saccaṃ kira, nigrodha, bhāsitā te esā vācā”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it really true, Nigrodha—are those your words?”"

msgctxt "dn25:71.3"
msgid ""
"“Saccaṃ, bhante, bhāsitā me esā vācā, yathābālena yathāmūḷhena "
"yathāakusalenā”ti."
msgstr ""
"“It’s true, sir, those are my words. It was foolish, stupid, and unskillful "
"of me.”"

msgctxt "dn25:71.4"
msgid "“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, nigrodha."
msgstr "“What do you think, Nigrodha?"

msgctxt "dn25:71.5"
msgid ""
"Kinti te sutaṃ paribbājakānaṃ vuḍḍhānaṃ mahallakānaṃ ācariyapācariyānaṃ "
"bhāsamānānaṃ:"
msgstr ""
"Have you heard that wanderers of the past who were elderly and senior, the "
"teachers of teachers, said that"

#. VAR: viharanti → vihariṃsu (bj, s1-3, c1)
msgctxt "dn25:71.6"
msgid ""
"‘ye te ahesuṃ atītamaddhānaṃ arahanto sammāsambuddhā, evaṃ su te bhagavanto "
"saṅgamma samāgamma unnādino uccāsaddamahāsaddā anekavihitaṃ tiracchānakathaṃ "
"anuyuttā viharanti."
msgstr ""
"when the perfect ones, the fully awakened Buddhas of the past came together, "
"they made an uproar, a dreadful racket as they sat and talked about all "
"kinds of unworthy topics,"

msgctxt "dn25:71.7"
msgid "Seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn25:71.8"
msgid "rājakathaṃ corakathaṃ …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn25:71.9"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn25:71.10"
msgid "itibhavābhavakathaṃ iti vā."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn25:71.11"
msgid "Seyyathāpi tvaṃ etarahi sācariyako."
msgstr "like you do in your tradition these days?"

msgctxt "dn25:71.12"
msgid ""
"Udāhu, evaṃ su te bhagavanto araññavanapatthāni pantāni senāsanāni "
"paṭisevanti appasaddāni appanigghosāni vijanavātāni manussarāhasseyyakāni "
"paṭisallānasāruppāni, seyyathāpāhaṃ etarahī’”ti."
msgstr ""
"Or did they say that the Buddhas frequented remote lodgings in the "
"wilderness and the forest that are quiet and still, far from the madding "
"crowd, remote from human settlements, and appropriate for retreat, like I do "
"these days?”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="62"></a>
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn25:72.1"
msgid "“Sutaṃ metaṃ, bhante."
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn25:72.2"
msgid "Paribbājakānaṃ vuḍḍhānaṃ mahallakānaṃ ācariyapācariyānaṃ bhāsamānānaṃ:"
msgstr ""
"“I have heard that wanderers of the past who were elderly and senior, said "
"that"

#. VAR: na evaṃ su te → na evaṃsute (s1-3) | nāssu te (pts1)
msgctxt "dn25:72.3"
msgid ""
"‘ye te ahesuṃ atītamaddhānaṃ arahanto sammāsambuddhā, na evaṃ su te "
"bhagavanto saṅgamma samāgamma unnādino uccāsaddamahāsaddā anekavihitaṃ "
"tiracchānakathaṃ anuyuttā viharanti."
msgstr ""
"when the perfect ones, the fully awakened Buddhas of the past came together, "
"they didn’t make an uproar,"

msgctxt "dn25:72.4"
msgid "Seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn25:72.5"
msgid "rājakathaṃ corakathaṃ …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn25:72.6"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn25:72.7"
msgid "itibhavābhavakathaṃ iti vā, seyyathāpāhaṃ etarahi sācariyako."
msgstr "like I do in my tradition these days."

msgctxt "dn25:72.8"
msgid ""
"Evaṃ su te bhagavanto araññavanapatthāni pantāni senāsanāni paṭisevanti "
"appasaddāni appanigghosāni vijanavātāni manussarāhasseyyakāni "
"paṭisallānasāruppāni, seyyathāpi bhagavā etarahī’”ti."
msgstr ""
"They say that the Buddhas of the past frequented remote lodgings in the "
"wilderness, like the Buddha does these days.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="63"></a><a class="pts" id="pts3.55"></a>
msgctxt "dn25:73.1"
msgid "“Tassa te, nigrodha, viññussa sato mahallakassa na etadahosi:"
msgstr "“Nigrodha, you are a sensible and mature man. Did it not occur to you:"

msgctxt "dn25:73.2"
msgid ""
"‘buddho so bhagavā bodhāya dhammaṃ deseti, danto so bhagavā damathāya "
"dhammaṃ deseti, santo so bhagavā samathāya dhammaṃ deseti, tiṇṇo so bhagavā "
"taraṇāya dhammaṃ deseti, parinibbuto so bhagavā parinibbānāya dhammaṃ "
"desetī’”ti?"
msgstr ""
"‘The Blessed One is awakened, tamed, serene, crossed over, and extinguished. "
"And he teaches Dhamma for awakening, taming, serenity, crossing over, and "
"extinguishment’?”"

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn25:74.1"
msgid "5. Brahmacariyapariyosānasacchikiriyā"
msgstr "The Culmination of the Spiritual Path"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="64"></a><a class="wp" id="wp22"></a>
msgctxt "dn25:75.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, nigrodho paribbājako bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "Nigrodha said:"

msgctxt "dn25:75.2"
msgid ""
"“accayo maṃ, bhante, accagamā yathābālaṃ yathāmūḷhaṃ yathāakusalaṃ, yvāhaṃ "
"evaṃ bhagavantaṃ avacāsiṃ."
msgstr ""
"“I have made a mistake, sir. It was foolish, stupid, and unskillful of me to "
"speak in that way."

msgctxt "dn25:75.3"
msgid ""
"Tassa me, bhante, bhagavā accayaṃ accayato paṭiggaṇhātu āyatiṃ saṃvarāyā”ti."
msgstr ""
"Please, sir, accept my mistake for what it is, so I will restrain myself in "
"future.”"

#. VAR: tvaṃ → taṃ (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "dn25:75.4"
msgid ""
"“Taggha tvaṃ, nigrodha, accayo accagamā yathābālaṃ yathāmūḷhaṃ "
"yathāakusalaṃ, yo maṃ tvaṃ evaṃ avacāsi."
msgstr ""
"“Indeed, Nigrodha, you made a mistake. It was foolish, stupid, and "
"unskillful of you to speak in that way."

msgctxt "dn25:75.5"
msgid ""
"Yato ca kho tvaṃ, nigrodha, accayaṃ accayato disvā yathādhammaṃ paṭikarosi, "
"taṃ te mayaṃ paṭiggaṇhāma."
msgstr ""
"But since you have recognized your mistake for what it is, and have dealt "
"with it properly, I accept it."

msgctxt "dn25:75.6"
msgid ""
"Vuddhi hesā, nigrodha, ariyassa vinaye, yo accayaṃ accayato disvā "
"yathādhammaṃ paṭikaroti āyatiṃ saṃvaraṃ āpajjati."
msgstr ""
"For it is growth in the training of the noble one to recognize a mistake for "
"what it is, deal with it properly, and commit to restraint in the future.”"

msgctxt "dn25:75.7"
msgid "Ahaṃ kho pana, nigrodha, evaṃ vadāmi:"
msgstr "Nigrodha, this is what I say:"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="65"></a><a class="pts" id="pts3.56"></a>
msgctxt "dn25:76.1"
msgid ""
"‘Etu viññū puriso asaṭho amāyāvī ujujātiko, ahamanusāsāmi ahaṃ dhammaṃ "
"desemi."
msgstr ""
"Let a sensible person come—neither devious nor deceitful, a person of "
"integrity. I teach and instruct them. "

#. VAR: Yathānusiṭṭhaṃ tathā → yathānusiṭṭhaṃ (?)
msgctxt "dn25:76.2"
msgid "Yathānusiṭṭhaṃ tathā paṭipajjamāno—"
msgstr "By practicing as instructed they will"

msgctxt "dn25:76.3"
msgid ""
"yassatthāya kulaputtā sammadeva agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajanti, tadanuttaraṃ—"
msgstr ""
"realize the supreme end of the spiritual path in this very life, in seven "
"years. They will live having achieved with their own insight the goal for "
"which people from respectable families rightly go forth from the lay life to "
"homelessness."

msgctxt "dn25:76.4"
msgid ""
"brahmacariyapariyosānaṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā "
"upasampajja viharissati sattavassāni."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn25:76.5"
msgid "Tiṭṭhantu, nigrodha, satta vassāni."
msgstr "Let alone seven years,"

